com.github.triceo.splitlog.api

Interface MessageConsumer<P extends MessageProducer<P>>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - The source that they expect such notifications from.
    All Superinterfaces:
    MessageListener<P>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CommonFollower<P,C>, Follower, MergingFollower, MessageMetric<T,S>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MetricExpectationManager, MidDeliveryExpectationManager

    public interface MessageConsumer<P extends MessageProducer<P>>
extends MessageListener<P>
    Implementors of this interface state that they are interested in knowing when a new Message appears in the log. Users shouldn't implement this interface. Instead, they should implement MessageListener and obtain their MessageConsumers from MessageProducers.

        Returns:
        False if isStopped().
